      "content": "Yeah, that makes sense. Fixing that `packetBuffer` will definitely help that specific function, but we're still seeing a drift in memory usage even after applying some quick fixes. \n\nThe problem is the scale; the codebase is massive, and these leaks are so small and gradual that they're incredibly hard to pin down. They seem to just pop up out of nowhere during long-term stress tests and then vanish once we restart. Since we're on an embedded system with limited instrumentation, what are some more \"aggressive\" ways to hunt down these elusive leaks that might be hiding in the background or slipping past standard static analysis?",
      "source": "evaluator"
